magpie.data.utilities.splitters

Class BaseDatasetSplitter

  • java.lang.Object
    • magpie.data.utilities.splitters.BaseDatasetSplitter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Cloneable, Commandable, Options, Printable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    AllMetalsSplitter, AttributeIntervalSplitter, ClustererSplitter, MeasuredClassSplitter, NonZeroClassificationSplitter, ObjectiveFunctionSplitter, PredictedClassIntervalSplitter, SingleElementGroupSplitter

    public abstract class BaseDatasetSplitter
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, Options, Commandable, java.lang.Cloneable, Printable
    This class provides an interface to Dataset splitting operations. Any implementation must fill the following operations:
    • label(magpie.data.Dataset) - Returns a list of integers that specify which subset each entry belongs to
    • Options.setOptions(java.util.List<java.lang.Object>) - Define settings for this splitter
    • train(magpie.data.Dataset) - Train a Dataset splitter, if needed

    Implemented Commands

    <output> = get <partition number> $<dataset> - Get a certain partition from a dataset
    partition number: Index (starting at 0) of desired partition
    dataset: Dataset to be split

    save $<data> <filename> [<format>] - Split a dataset, then print it out to files
    data: Datasetto be printed
    filename: Names of files. Output will be this + split number for each split.
    format: Optional: Format in which to write data (default=serialized)

    train $<data> - Train splitter
    data: Dataset used to train splitter

    Print Commands details - Description of this splitter names - Names of the splits

    See Also:

        public java.lang.String printDescription(boolean htmlFormat)

        Example: For a model training a separate WekaRegression for intermetallics

        Contains Nonmetal: magpie.regression.LASSORegreession -maxterms 2
